mods:titleInfo.mods:title: A Vertical Product Differentiation Model for Geospatial Information Services

mods:name.mods:namePart: Westfalen / Universität Münster / Universitäts- und Landesbibliothek

mods:mods.mods:abstract: Though the commercial dissemination of geospatial data by means of Internet shops has been pursued by numerous content providers for many years now, web service-oriented architectures underpinning such marketing platforms are just emerging. Many efforts are currently spent on the enabling technology and the necessary standards and implementation specifications for allowing a seamless integration of distinct software components in so-called geospatial data infrastructures. Marketing issues are in fact less pronounced at present. Therefore, this work aims at delivering scientific insights on vertical product differentiation and how this established marketing method fits into the electronic markets being currently built upon such infrastructures. The conceptual model developed in this work shall highlight the capability of the aforementioned method when it is applied to market-oriented geospatial information services.
mods:mods.mods:note: Druckausg.: Münster: Institut für Geoinformatik, 2007. (IfGiprints ; 31) ISBN 978-3-936616-50-7
